The Lord kills and gives life.
- He thrusts men down to hell and raises them up again.

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
PSALMODY & ANTIPHONS of Good Friday

READING:    1 Pet 1:18-21    Realizing that you were ransomed from your futile conduct, handed on by your ancestors, not with perishable things like silver or gold but with the precious blood of Christ as of a spotless unblemished lamb. He was known before the foundation of the world but revealed in the final time for you, who through him believe in God who raised him from the dead and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God. Mutual Love. Since you have purified yourselves by obedience to the truth for sincere mutual love, love one another intensely from a [pure] heart.

MAGNIFICAT:	Now the Son of Man has been glorified and God has been glorified in him.

Compline from Sunday, after Second Vespers. It is said only by those who do not participate in the Easter Vigil.

